captions: Reset PC back to previous value.

ALU_N.desciption: If ALU_N is asserted the B input to the adder is inverted. This signal should be asserted when resetting the ALU so that the internal carry can be set up for subtraction.

~ALU_RESET.desciption: Deasserting ~ALU_RESET resets the ALU, which clears the internal registers. The ALU should be reset right before any ALU operation.

ALU_AUX.desciption: The ALU_AUX signal has two uses: on a rising edge of ALU_AUX both the flag register of the ALU, and the state machine used for bit shift instructions are clocked

~REG_IN_EN.desciption: While ~REG_IN_EN is deasserted the data selected by REG_IN_MUX is clocked in to the selected register.

PC_OUT_LATCH.desciption: On a rising edge of PC_OUT_LATCH the current value of the internal PC counter is made available on the outgoing PC bus.

PC_IN_LATCH.desciption: On a rising edge of PC_IN_LATCH a new address is latched in to the internal program counter.

ADDR_LATCH.desciption: On a rising edge of ADDR_LATCH a new address is latched in to the memory controller.

ADDR_CLK.desciption: The address loaded to the memory controller is increased by one on each rising edge of ADDR_CLK. While reading new opcodes the address clock is gated so that only two bytes is read for a compressed instruction.

~MEM_OE.desciption: When ~MEM_OE is deasserted the device corresponding to the currently selected memory address should output data. The data is sampled on the rising edge of ~MEM_OE.

~MEM_WE.desciption: ~MEM_WE is deasserted when writing to a memory location. The written data will be  available on the external data bus for half a clock cycle after ~MEM_WE goes high.

OP_LATCH.desciption: On the rising edge of OP_LATCH a new opcode is latched in and decoded.

OP_LATCH_LSB.desciption: Latch in the lowest byte of the new opcode. This signal should be held high while reading the third and fourth byte of the opcode.

BUS_EN.desciption: During a clock cycle with BUS_EN high the various shift registers are being clocked with new data. A clock cycle with BUS_EN low is used for only changing control signals.

PC_CNT_EN.desciption: The internal PC counter is incremented on a rising clock edge if PC_CNT_EN is high. This signal is automatically asserted during the first step of any opcode.
